HEADWORD: decentralization
<hw>de*cen`tral*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The action of decentralizing, or the state of being
decentralized.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>decentralization</xex> of
France.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. P. Peters.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the spread of power away from the center to local
branches or governments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decentralize</ent>⟦br⟧
